==English==
===Pronunciation===
*[[w:AHD|AHD]]: bĕ'ri
*[[w:IPA|IPA]]: /ˈberi/
*[[w:SAMPA|SAMPA]]: /"beri/
*{{audio|en-us-bury.ogg|Audio (US)}}
===Etymology===
Old English ''[[byrġan]]''
====Homophones====
*[[berry]]

===Transitive Verb===
'''to bury''' ([[buried]], [[burying]], [[buries]])
#To ritualistically inter a [[corpse]] in a [[grave]] or [[tomb]]. (see [[burial]])
#To [[place]] in the [[ground]]. "''bury a bone''"
#To [[hide]] or [[conceal]] as if by covering with earth - "''she buried her face in the pillow''", "''buried the secret deep inside''"
#To put an end to; to [[adandon]]. "''They buried their argument and shook hands''"

